    <title>Google’s internal political battles keep spilling out into the public</title>
    <content type="html">  
    &lt;img alt="" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/U7cbVNnNDa0feYw5j082DGXEor4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/61377463/mdoying_180117_2249_0272stills.0.jpg" /&gt;



  &lt;p id="htD4lT"&gt;It’s an unhappy time at Google.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="kXFt7x"&gt;Ever since &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2017/8/5/16101978/google-employee-wrote-anti-diversity-manifesto?utm_campaign=The%20Interface&amp;amp;utm_medium=email&amp;amp;utm_source=Revue%20newsletter"&gt;the James Damore controversy&lt;/a&gt; last year, Google has faced regular eruptions from unhappy employees who wish to protest the company’s politics in public. In January, a former security engineer said he &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2018/1/12/16882270/google-diversity-hiring-executives-cory-altheide?utm_campaign=The%20Interface&amp;amp;utm_medium=email&amp;amp;utm_source=Revue%20newsletter"&gt;had been stopped from sharing his pro-diversity views&lt;/a&gt;. This summer, a group of employees successfully pressured the company to &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2018/6/1/17418406/google-maven-drone-imagery-ai-contract-expire?utm_campaign=The%20Interface&amp;amp;utm_medium=email&amp;amp;utm_source=Revue%20newsletter"&gt;stop building an AI project for the military&lt;/a&gt;. A similar group is now pushing &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2018/8/16/17702464/google-search-censorship-china-protest-project-dragonfly?utm_campaign=The%20Interface&amp;amp;utm_medium=email&amp;amp;utm_source=Revue%20newsletter"&gt;to prevent the company from re-entering China&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="yZDqcy"&gt;All of this has played out in unusually public ways — and against a political backdrop that has grown increasingly unfriendly to Google and its parent company, Alphabet. President Trump &lt;a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/05/technology/google-trump-bias.html?utm_campaign=The%20Interface&amp;amp;utm_medium=email&amp;amp;utm_source=Revue%20newsletter"&gt;has repeatedly tweeted baseless allegations&lt;/a&gt; that the company is...&lt;/p&gt;
